# Cloudflare Pages cache policy.
#
# The service worker and the HTML shell must NEVER be pinned by the CDN/browser,
# so a fresh deploy is picked up on the next visit: the SW update check always
# revalidates sw.js, sees the new build, and `registerType: 'autoUpdate'` swaps
# the app. (Default Pages policy cached sw.js for 4h, which delayed that.)
#
# Content-hashed assets (…-<hash>.js/.css) carry the build hash in their name, so
# they can be cached forever — a new build ships new filenames.

# Security hardening — applied to every response. These are safe, non-breaking
# headers (they don't gate any resource the app loads). A Content-Security-Policy
# is deliberately NOT set here: this SPA relies on inline `style="--k-*"` attrs,
# Google Fonts, remote avatars, and the kit CDN, so a CSP needs a real deploy
# test cycle before it can ship without breaking the live site.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
